comment:
How can anyone possibly believe that Amber is innocent in this??? Even according to her own "proof" the worst thing he does is slam a cabinet (hardly anything that would make someone fear for their life..) besides which if she's so scared for her life - WHY WOULD SHE NEVER LET HIM LEAVE?!?! Why stand there and laugh just to record someone's personal suffering?? You don't do that to people to love!! Never has she once proven to be a nice/genuine person at all. All I'm going off is the evidence itself. If you throw a phone at someone it's not possible for it to leave an exact imprint of the phone(as someone who's actually been hit with one, I have a little experience) he'd have had to literally strike her directly and repeatedly with the phone still in his hand, we all know (according to her own admission even) that he didn't. Plus, the picture of the rectangular "phone" bruise are in a completely different spot (much higher on the cheek bone) than the "bruise" she had a few days later when she went to court for the incident. Bruises down just relocate. Unless they're fake...
 Has anyone else noticed how Amber has no range of emotions at all? She always looks either amused or bored in her "evidence"/deposition. If something happened where you're afraid for your life how can you not show a single emotion about it???? I was almost kidnapped ten years ago and I still get choked up telling the story. Bottom line - nothing she say adds up!!! How can anyone believe her??? "I thought he was about to push my sister down the stairs" - first off, it's suspicious that she goes to dramatic length in defending her own actions (from her deposition-"my baby sister was about to die, I did what any mother/sister would do!"- yet couldn't even describe the actual actions committed against her that caused her to "fear for her life". Not like "he turned towards us quickly with his fists raised" not a single thing to describe what he actually was doing at that moment  that made her so afraid - her only justification is rumors! "I heard rumors he pushed someone else down the stairs before"... That defense would never stand in any American criminal trial. And the British tabloids keep railing on Johnny and his fans because their laws only require "good faith" and not actual proof in order to legally defame somebody (all they have to do is tell the judge they believed it to be true). Seriously, please explain to me how anyone could defend her ü§Æ she'll get what's coming to her. And furthermore evidence of her delusions, she believes she'd never get kicked off Aquaman because " the fans love me and they're the ones who make it happen" - GIRL the only two reasons anyone saw that movie was to see Jason Momoa or because they're fans of Namor - nobody ever heard of you until thisüßê. From this day forward, people who claim to be victims when they're truly the perpetrator will be known as "Hearders"! (Sorry it's so long I just truly am incredibly dumdfounded...)

comment:
If you look up scientific literature as well as books/journals from mental health professionals, those with Naercissist Personality Disorder often will admit exactly EXACTLY what they plan yo do and say "I wouldn't do this" or "yeah right like I am trying to xxxxx."

Amber does this about 5:00 mins in when she says no one will believe shes trying to get money from him. This is a classic sign of someone who has NPD. 

As a survivor of an abusive mother and ex both of whom had Cluster B PD, I am with Johnny and hope he finds a therapist he trusts and can help him learn to love himself more. Johnny wasn't taught boundaries from his own toxic mother, a painful thing to admit at any age...that our mothers failed us and never truly loved us. But if anyone thinks her behavior is normal, you are in a toxic relationship - be it with your mother, friend, or partner. And you deserve better. ‚ù§
